{"uuid":"360e8515-6962-4365-8e0a-87d94a891b47","type":"360e8515-6962-4365-8e0a-87d94a891b47","name":"Type Specification","description":"The root of Vostan Type system. All types (including this type itself) are of this type.","properties":[{"name":"UUID","value_type":"4279780d-d0cf-462d-b2bd-135a418b6e87","mandatory":"b06d4094-116b-4d2e-93ea-4398286e9acf","description":"As any record in Vostan, type specification also required to have a UUID and know/specify its own UUID in its record. This is an internal SW requirement, and also is useful in the GUI for informational purposes.","id":"uuid","readonly":"508fddb1-933b-433c-a12c-2c76ad631519","visible":"b06d4094-116b-4d2e-93ea-4398286e9acf"},{"name":"Type of this record","value_type":"360e8515-6962-4365-8e0a-87d94a891b47","mandatory":"b06d4094-116b-4d2e-93ea-4398286e9acf","description":"TODO: consider making this read-only because it' stypically programmatically set and never changable.","id":"type","readonly":"508fddb1-933b-433c-a12c-2c76ad631519","visible":"b06d4094-116b-4d2e-93ea-4398286e9acf"},{"name":"Identifier","value_type":"57edf1cb-ac1e-49fa-bbb8-09658ed2ac19","mandatory":"b06d4094-116b-4d2e-93ea-4398286e9acf","description":"Identifiers are used to uniquely define the object in a collection of alike objects. E.g. in collection of Employees of a company each employee may have it's own ID by which he is identified in the HR.","id":"id","readonly":"508fddb1-933b-433c-a12c-2c76ad631519","visible":"b06d4094-116b-4d2e-93ea-4398286e9acf"},{"name":"Name","value_type":"57edf1cb-ac1e-49fa-bbb8-09658ed2ac19","mandatory":"b06d4094-116b-4d2e-93ea-4398286e9acf","description":"human readable name of this type, in future will also support localization","id":"name","readonly":"508fddb1-933b-433c-a12c-2c76ad631519","visible":"b06d4094-116b-4d2e-93ea-4398286e9acf"},{"name":"Description","value_type":"6d084f31-309f-4cd4-8bcf-a703047af2cc","mandatory":"b06d4094-116b-4d2e-93ea-4398286e9acf","description":"Description of the type for users/help/training. Used in the GUI to show hint and to generate help-pages. ","id":"description","readonly":"508fddb1-933b-433c-a12c-2c76ad631519","visible":"b06d4094-116b-4d2e-93ea-4398286e9acf"},{"name":"Is Literal","value_type":"beb2c92b-3e3e-41b8-9692-cd69b1f2c6f8","mandatory":"508fddb1-933b-433c-a12c-2c76ad631519","description":"specifies whether this is a scalar type that should be literally set in the embedded record field, or should be rather referred to by UUID as a standalone value. E.g. string types are literal types because fields of string types are stored in the object, not under separate UUID. Whereas the Boolean type is not literal, because True and False constants have own UUID, and therefore boolean fields refer to them by UUID, and not literally putting \"true\" or \"false\" in the field name.","id":"literal","readonly":"508fddb1-933b-433c-a12c-2c76ad631519","default_value":"508fddb1-933b-433c-a12c-2c76ad631519","visible":"b06d4094-116b-4d2e-93ea-4398286e9acf"},{"id":"icon","name":"Icon","value_type":"deef4328-2301-45da-8864-98b9bac4e369","mandatory":"508fddb1-933b-433c-a12c-2c76ad631519","default_value":"","readonly":"508fddb1-933b-433c-a12c-2c76ad631519","description":"The default icon used for the objects of this type.  If developer creates a property-specification of with title \"icon\" then objects which have such property set will override this. Otherwise this icon will be used for all objects of such type.","visible":"b06d4094-116b-4d2e-93ea-4398286e9acf","icon":"","video":""}],"collections":[{"name":"Property Specifications","element_type":"0c06a71f-15a0-4ddd-bb00-bd1bb39ab925","description":"This collection contains specifications of this Type's properties: their name, type, default-values, etc.","id":"properties","kind":"3dae7672-7536-4159-a9da-94dc4c8e133a","symmetric":""},{"name":"Collection Specifications","element_type":"ce629dbc-1722-464a-b853-b9e849eaf9a7","kind":"3dae7672-7536-4159-a9da-94dc4c8e133a","description":"This collection contains specifications of the collections of this type, specifically the name of the collection, the type of the elements that are stored in the collection, the kind of the collection (e.g. are the elements stored separately under their own UUIDs or as part of this Type's record - embedded), etc. ","id":"collections","symmetric":""},{"name":"Value Set","element_type":"6e41f5f6-ddf8-494b-a12e-1327ffb85ca3","kind":"51e4062d-2e7a-4876-9a20-aca1eb928d4a","description":"This allows specifying set of allowed values for this type. Thus we implement Enumerated type support not only for literal/scalar types but for any types: by specifying this limited list of allowed/possible values we turn any type into an enumerated type.","id":"values","symmetric":""},{"id":"methods","name":"Methods","element_type":"1fda6af7-f8dd-4aca-80ad-290d827779a6","kind":"51e4062d-2e7a-4876-9a20-aca1eb928d4a","description":"Collection for methods of this class.","symmetric":""}],"values":[],"id":"Type","literal":"508fddb1-933b-433c-a12c-2c76ad631519","visible":"b06d4094-116b-4d2e-93ea-4398286e9acf","methods":[]}